        <p class="muted">This page highlights major legislative and policy achievements often cited by supporters — tax reform, trade agreements, criminal justice reform, and strong pre-pandemic economic indicators.</p>

        <div class="grid" style="margin-top:18px">
          <div class="tile card" id="tax-cut">
            <h3>Tax Reform (2017)</h3>
            <p>Signed the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, a broad overhaul of the tax code that reduced corporate rates and changed individual brackets and deductions — measures supporters credit for stimulating investment and growth. <span class="muted" id="c1"></span></p>
          </div>

          <div class="tile card" id="jobs">
            <h3>Jobs & Economy</h3>
            <p>Before the COVID pandemic, unemployment fell to lows not seen in decades and median household income rose — items frequently highlighted as indicators of economic strength during the administration. <span class="muted" id="c2"></span></p>
          </div>

          <div class="tile card" id="trade">
            <h3>USMCA Trade Deal</h3>
            <p>Negotiated and implemented the USMCA to modernize North American trade rules and replace NAFTA, aiming to support manufacturing and high-paying jobs. <span class="muted" id="c3"></span></p>
          </div>

          <div class="tile card" id="justice">
            <h3>First Step Act (2018)</h3>
            <p>Signed bipartisan criminal justice reform to reduce recidivism and modify some sentencing provisions — a notable bipartisan achievement. <span class="muted" id="c4"></span></p>
          </div>

          <div class="tile card" id="markets">
            <h3>Markets & Investment</h3>
            <p>U.S. equity markets experienced substantial gains during the administration's first term, a point commonly used to demonstrate investor confidence. <span class="muted" id="c5"></span></p>
          </div>

          <div class="tile card" id="more">
            <h3>More</h3>
            <p>Regulatory rollbacks, energy policy focused on domestic production, and judicial appointments are additional themes supporters cite as long-term impacts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

