        <article style="margin-top:12px">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:6px">Jobs & Unemployment</h3>
          <p class="muted">U.S. unemployment reached multi-decade lows before the COVID-19 pandemic; BLS data provide month-by-month figures showing those trends.</p>
          <p class="sources">Source: Bureau of Labor Statistics unemployment series. :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}</p>
        </article>

        <article style="margin-top:12px">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:6px">USMCA (North American Trade)</h3>
          <p class="muted">The USMCA modernized NAFTA rules and officially entered into force in July 2020, with aims to support North American workers and trade. </p>
          <p class="sources">Source: Office of the U.S. Trade Representative (USTR) and Congressional Research Service summaries. :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}</p>
        </article>

        <article style="margin-top:12px">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:6px">First Step Act (2018)</h3>
          <p class="muted">A bipartisan criminal justice reform law focused on recidivism reduction, prison programming, and some sentencing adjustments was signed in 2018.</p>
          <p class="sources">Sources: Bureau of Prisons overview; CRS analysis. :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}</p>
        </article>

        <article style="margin-top:12px">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:6px">Markets & Investment</h3>
          <p class="muted">Major U.S. equity indexes recorded significant gains across the administration's first term — a commonly cited metric by supporters to indicate market confidence.</p>
          <p class="sources">Sources: S&P 500 performance summaries and market commentary. :contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}</p>
